Description: Bronze model axe-head: made out of thin sheet metal. It has splayed sides and a slightly concave elongated butt with thin tapering lugs. It is moderately corroded. Some of the cutting edge is lost.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: F. Addison, 'The Wellcome Excavations in the Sudan. I. Jebel Moya' (oxford, 1949), 141, pl. LX, A6.1
Bibliographic references: Davies 1987 / Catalogue of Egyptian Antiquities in the British Museum (149)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Henry Solomon Wellcome
